snippet: Meseret Defar won the 5,000 meters, defeating Tirunesh Dibaba, a fellow Ethiopian who was fatigued from her gold-medal effort in the 10,000 as well as an undisclosed pre-Olympics illness.
abstract: Ethiopian distance runner Meseret Defar wins the women's 5,000 meters, recapturing the gold medal from her countrywoman Tirunesh Dibaba, who takes bronze; Kenya's Vivian Cheruiyot wins silver; other results noted.
lead_paragraph: Meseret Defar won the 5,000 meters, defeating Tirunesh Dibaba, a fellow Ethiopian who was fatigued from her gold-medal effort in the 10,000 as well as an undisclosed pre-Olympics illness.

headline.seo: Ethiopian Reclaims 5,000-Meter Olympic Title From Rival
headline.main: Ethiopian Reclaims 5,000-Meter Title From a Rival Countrywoman
